spec: decimal_extra2431
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(decimal)
error_model: python_exceptions
provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "Python docs — https://docs.python.org/3/library/decimal.html"
    - "CPython source — Modules/_decimal/_decimal.c"
  not_derived_from:
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 2431: __aiter__ and __anext__ async iteration protocol dict-presence for decimal types."
    - "decimal.Decimal and decimal.Context do not define __aiter__ or __anext__ in their class __dict__."
    - "decimal.DecimalException and all its subclasses (InvalidOperation, DivisionByZero, Overflow, Underflow, Inexact, Subnormal, Rounded, Clamped, FloatOperation, ConversionSyntax, DivisionImpossible, DivisionUndefined, InvalidContext) are exception classes and define no async iteration."
    - "decimal.DecimalTuple is a namedtuple subclass and does not define __aiter__ or __anext__ in its own __dict__."
    - "The decimal module is a numeric type module; none of its types participate in the async iteration protocol."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"

